                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1167">In hagiography: Bassus and his twin <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1492">Suzanna</persName> 
                        were twin children of a Zoroastrian governor. They were informed about Christianity by a
                        Christian slave. They were baptized by an ascetic named Longinus. They were killed by
                        their father. At least one <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/571">monastery
                            commemorating Mar Bassus</placeName> was founded near <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/11">Apamea</placeName>.</note>
